snippet.textDisplay:
I agree with Nigel Fagage when he says UK are ~ 2 weeks behind Italy on the coronavirus curve. It is not rocket science!

One formula for calculating the mortality rate during an outbreak is:- CFR = deaths / (deaths + recovered). With the latest data for Italy CFR = 463/(463+724)= 42/1187=39% - an order of magnitude greater than WHO estimate of 3.4%.

For UK: CFR=5/(5+18)= 22%.. Time for UK government action!

snippet.textDisplay:
I had developed dry cough on Thursday, I was ok during the weekend but on Monday when I was travelling to work I found difficulties breathing. I called 111 England it took me 3hr to get through to them, they sent me to hospital by ambulance. I had a mask on because I was coughing non-stop but at hospital the staff felt uncomfortable seeing face masks on they asked me to remove it. They didn't do test on me for coronavirue as I did not travel from infected countries and been in contact with confirmed case of coronavirue they just said viral infection and gave me no medication. I work in a very large school I have number stuff whom have traveled all over the world Singapore, Italy and France, Spain and Thailand last to week. It was wrong of the 111 England to send me to hospital before testing me for the coronavirue. I wanted to be tested for coronavirue as I feel I come into contact with so many people every day whom could of have this virus. There at hospital were many elderly people who will now contract whatever virus I have.
What is UK doing!
